<figureCitation id="136B3CDBC3015A71FCC7FAFEFC0DFAF0" box="[813,918,1348,1372]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[168,231,1099,1119]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,160,1075]" captionTargetId="figure-430@6.[168,1422,160,1075]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 4. Fish species collected in upper Piraí river drainage. A. Harttia carvalhoi, MNRJ 43816, 78.1 mm SL. B. Harttia loricariformis, MNRJ 43773, 42.1 mm SL. C. Hemipsilichthys gobio, MNRJ 43868, 75.3 mm SL (Adult individual collected in the rio do BraÇo, 22° 47’ 09”S 44° 10’ 44”W, a tributary of the Piraí river. The exemplar of H. gobio, MNRJ 36482, collected in this study is a small juvenile.). D. Hemipsilichthys papillatus, MNRJ 46657, 53.7 mm SL. E. Hypostomus affinis, MNRJ 43824, 62.6 mm SL. F. Hypostomus luetkeni, MNRJ 47007, 112.8 mm SL. G. Neoplecostomus microps, MNRJ 43808, 87 mm SL. H. Pareiorhina rudolphi, MNRJ 46835, 65.9 mm SL. I. Rineloricaria sp. cf. R. lima, MNRJ 43826, 76.3 mm SL." pageId="6" pageNumber="241">Figure 4E</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF205EC3015A71FCB8FADCFAF1FA0C" blockId="6.[813,1420,1348,1681]" pageId="6" pageNumber="241">
Geographic distribution: 
<collectingRegion id="4994EEBCC3015A71FB87FADCFB25FAD2" box="[1133,1214,1382,1406]" country="Brazil" name="Paraiba" pageId="6" pageNumber="241">Paraíba</collectingRegion>
do Sul and Doce river basins and coastal rivers of southeastern 
<collectingCountry id="F34760CEC3015A71FACAFA32FAFDFA0C" box="[1312,1382,1416,1440]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="241">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF205EC3015A71FCB8FA11FC2AF93C" blockId="6.[813,1420,1348,1681]" pageId="6" pageNumber="241">
Diagnosis: Individuals of 
<taxonomicName id="4C505BDDC3015A71FB86FA16FAA6FA6F" baseAuthorityName="Steindachner" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[1132,1341,1451,1475]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hypostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="241" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis id="B924FC4CC3015A71FB86FA16FAA6FA6F" box="[1132,1341,1451,1475]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="241">Hypostomus affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished 
<taxonomicName id="4C505BDDC3015A71FC2EFA74FBA1FA49" box="[964,1082,1485,1509]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hypostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="241" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="luetkeni">
<emphasis id="B924FC4CC3015A71FC2EFA74FBA1FA49" box="[964,1082,1485,1509]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="241">H. luetkeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of 1 main postsupraoccipital plate and 4 lateral ridges on flanks (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC15DAFC3015A71FABBFA4AFC79F986" author="Mazzoni R &amp; Caramaschi U &amp; Weber C" pageId="6" pageNumber="241" pagination="3 - 18" refId="ref7715" refString="Mazzoni R, Caramaschi U, Weber C (1994) Taxonomical revision of the species of Hypostomus Lacepede, 1803 (Siluriformes, Loricariidae) from the Lower rio Paraiba do Sul, State of Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. Revue Suisse de Zoologie 101 (1): 3 - 18. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 79897" type="journal article" year="1994">Mazzoni et al. 1994</bibRefCitation>
). The prevailing pigmentation pattern in adults of 
<taxonomicName id="4C505BDDC3015A71FC59F98FFB83F9E0" baseAuthorityName="Steindachner" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[947,1048,1588,1612]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hypostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="241" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis id="B924FC4CC3015A71FC59F98FFB83F9E0" box="[947,1048,1588,1612]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="241">H. affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comprises numerous black spots, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="4C505BDDC3015A71FC66F9EDFB98F9C3" box="[908,1027,1623,1647]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hypostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="241" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="luetkeni">
<emphasis id="B924FC4CC3015A71FC66F9EDFB98F9C3" box="[908,1027,1623,1647]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="241">H. luetkeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a more uniform dark pigmentation pattern.
</paragraph>
